# Optional API keys for your vault.
#
# This file is the TEMPLATE — copy it to ".env" (no .example) and fill in your
# actual keys. The .env file is gitignored, so your real keys never leave your
# machine.
#
# To set up:
#   macOS / Linux:   cp .env.example .env
#   Windows (cmd):   copy .env.example .env
#   Windows (PS):    Copy-Item .env.example .env
#
# Then open .env in VS Code and replace the placeholders below.
#
# Everything in this file is OPTIONAL. The vault works without any of it.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ElevenLabs — voice briefings (optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it unlocks: /brief produces an MP3 you can listen to on a walk,
# read by a British female narrator. The full text briefing still gets
# written either way — the audio is a bonus, not a replacement.
#
# How to get a key:
#   1. Sign up at https://elevenlabs.io (free tier — no credit card)
#   2. Profile → API Keys → "Create API Key"
#   3. Paste the key below, replacing "your-elevenlabs-key-here"
#
# Free tier: 10,000 chars/month ≈ 2–3 weekly audio briefings.
# Skip this if you'd rather just read the briefing.

Eleven_Labs=your-elevenlabs-key-here
